      <topic id="what-s-the-license-">
         <title>What's the license?</title>
         <body>
            <paragraph>Couchbase Lite itself is released under the <external-ref href="http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.html"/>.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>Some libraries that Couchbase Lite uses (<external-ref href="https://github.com/ccgus/fmdb"/>, <external-ref href="https://bitbucket.org/snej/myutilities/overview"/>, and <external-ref href="https://github.com/robbiehanson/CocoaHTTPServer"/>) have MIT or BSD licenses. We might seek relicensing or rewrite those parts of the code to get everything under a single Apache license.</paragraph>
         </body>
